id: pm-hfg5
title: "pm next repeats the recommended item verbatim as ready[0] — emit an id reference instead"
description: "Token-efficiency defect in the pm next envelope: the fully-projected recommended item is duplicated byte-identical as the first entry of the ready list, in both toon and json output. Duplicate check: searched next/duplicate/ready/envelope items — pm-gdi7 (flag hints, list-closed projection), pm-nilh (lean mutation default), pm-a9mc (validate counts-only) are adjacent but none covers the next envelope; no prior item found."
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 2
tags[3]: agent-ux,"area:cli",token-efficiency
created_at: "2026-07-07T15:24:51.495Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-07T15:24:51.495Z"
author: maintainer-agent
acceptance_criteria: "pm next (toon and json) no longer contains two full projections of the same item; the ready-list contract (excludes recommended, or id-ref) is documented in command docs and SDK contracts; contract snapshot tests assert non-duplication; MCP pm_next envelope matches"
parent: pm-mpbb
risk: low
confidence: high
body: "## Evidence (2026-07-07)\npm next default (toon) output is 6123 bytes; the recommended block (id/title/type/status/priority/assignee/tags/updated_at/parent/open_blocker_count, ~450 bytes for pm-w89s) is repeated verbatim as ready[0] with every field identical. Same duplication in --json (8559 bytes). Every agent picking work pays the duplicated projection on every call.\n\n## Why it matters\npm next is the highest-frequency read on the agent hot path (every work-pick loop). At thousands of concurrent agents (pm-9rxu scale story) the duplicated projection is pure waste, and it also trains agents to distrust the envelope (same item appears twice with no marker).\n\n## Fix sketch\nOmit the recommended item from ready (documented contract: ready = candidates EXCLUDING recommended), or replace ready[0] with a bare id reference (recommended_ref). Apply in one shared projection site so toon/json/MCP envelopes stay aligned; update SDK contracts + snapshot tests. Small-workspace neutral; strictly fewer tokens."
